subject: Using gcc driver instead of using ld directly to let gcc driver search the system library such as libc, libgcc_s1 automatically on cross-build environment.
commitMessage:
Using gcc driver instead of using ld directly to let gcc driver search the system library such as libc, libgcc_s1 automatically on cross-build environment.

Signed-off-by: Bogon Kim <bogon82.kim@samsung.com>

comments.message:
Patch Set 1:

[BUILD CHECK RESULT] This change is built against OBS project Tizen: 

 repository     arch           result         

 standard       armv7hl        succeeded      

 standard       x86_64         succeeded      

 standard       armv7l         succeeded      

 standard       i586           succeeded

Patch Set 1:

The libgcc_s is needed to link in the makefile. In the non-cross toolchain environment the libgcc lib can be found out automatically because it's in the /usr/lib. however, in the cross-toolchain environment the libgcc lib can be found out at "/usr/lib/gcc/$TRIPLE/$VERSION/" and you must add -L option to find out. That's why csr-framework is failed on ARM. To handle the link path problem in the Makefile is very odd. It's better to handle this to gcc driver. So I changed the linker from ld to gcc
Patch Set 1: Verified+1 Code-Review+1

Patch Set 1:

Ryan, Elena. could you check this review request?
Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1
